.&quot; Not only that, but must RP-enforced MUDs have a rich tapestry of history, and actually stick to it, unlike Norrath (Is Luclin included when someone says Norrath?). Already, before the MUD I admin on has openned, I've created and written down about 3 or 4 LONG, completly original quests, most of which are more roleplaying than killing. <br><br>Custom, one of a kind items? No problem. For starters, it's usually pretty simple to create items. In my opinion, if a situation warrants it, you SHOULD get a custom item. Items named after you are a different story. I really can't understand why a thousand people would all be running around with something named, &quot;Helmet of Vall&quot; or the like. I suppose if you engraved your rune/signature into it, you could call it, &quot;Helmet of Vall&quot;, but I'd only allow something like that to happen if it was smithed or the like. But, otherwise, all you would really have to do is contact an immortal (Which is infintely easier than contacting a GM.)<br><br>Oh, yeah. Roleplaying? Just find a roleplaying-enforced MUD. It's not hard at all. Those are Shintou's wet dreams right there. People just roleplay. No d00ds or the likes. Remember all those guard-killers in EverQuest, and how you wished that people killing them would be caught by the NPCs? Well, we've got something even worse. You get caught by the Imms. If you want to slaughter guards, then expect a mob coming after you. Pretty much the roleplaying action-reaction thing right there.<br><br>Now, the thing most people may not like is that MUDs are text based, which is where your imagination comes in handy. Pretty much, it's along the lines of typing, &quot;look Soandsoobject&quot; to get a description. Some people like it, some don't. Then again, you don't have to fork over 40 bucks a month for it. Yep, it's absolutly free. That was what was earned my, &quot;Fuck Verant&quot; comment. Sure, we don't have graphics, but we also don't have constant lag, as much frustration, client crashes (Sometimes the servers crash, but that's usually when I or someone else do something stupid, like trying to make a new spell that doesn't quite work on the main server when it should be on the test server.), and so forth.  <p>Vall Shadowstrife<BR>Tier'Dal Scout of Luclin <BR>Agent of The Ring <BR>"I thought I saw my own worst enemy, a kind of demon. And it was me."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uroninsenshi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RoninSenshi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Kanji.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senshi No Adakia</span><br>  Posts: 364<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/2/02 10:37:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1264.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Kanji.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why EverQuest Legends is a waste of money:</span><hr size=1> Here Vall. I'll do it for you. Can you send me a Link or something to any MUDs so I can see for myself? thanks. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uroninsenshi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RoninSenshi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Kanji.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 2/2/02 11:43:00 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvallshadowstrife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vall Shadowstrife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Crime Lord</span><br>  Posts: 124<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/2/02 11:13:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1264.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span cla